IMPORTANT NOTICES REGARDING PERSONAL HEALTH DATA
-------------------------------------------------

This software is designed to store, organize, and analyze personal health
information including laboratory results, clinical events, medications,
body composition measurements, and continuous monitoring data.

1. NO WARRANTY
   This software is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind. The authors
   make no representations regarding the accuracy, completeness, or fitness for
   any particular purpose of this software or any analysis it produces. Do not
   make medical decisions based solely on outputs from this software.

2. NOT MEDICAL ADVICE
   This software is a personal data organization and analysis tool. It is not
   a medical device, clinical decision support system, or substitute for
   professional medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. Always consult a
   qualified healthcare provider regarding your health.

3. DATA SECURITY
   This software encrypts the database file at rest using AES-256 (SQLCipher)
   with a two-factor key model: a randomly generated secret key stored in the
   OS keychain combined with a user master passphrase. The encrypted file is
   opaque ciphertext and is safe for cloud backup and sync. You remain solely
   responsible for:
   - Safeguarding your master passphrase and Recovery Kit
   - Ensuring your backup strategy is appropriate for your threat model
   - Complying with any applicable privacy laws in your jurisdiction

4. NO PERSONAL DATA IS INCLUDED
   This repository contains only code, schema definitions, and documentation.
   No personal health data is included. Any database file (*.db) is excluded
   from version control via .gitignore and must never be committed.

5. THIRD-PARTY SERVICES
   This software may be configured to interact with third-party services
   (AI clients, lab data providers, wearable platforms). Use of those services
   is subject to their respective terms and privacy policies. Review those
   terms before connecting your health data to any external service. When
   using a cloud-based AI client, your health data leaves your machine during
   analysis — use a local AI model if this is a concern.
